          }
        },
        "en" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "new",
            "value" : "What does GMI mean?"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "faq.glossary.ig.answer" : {
      "comment" : "Answer explaining what IG means in the glossary",
      "extractionState" : "extracted_with_value",
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "IG steht für Interstitial Glucose (Gewebezucker). Gemeint sind Glukosewerte, die von einem kontinuierlichen Glukosemess-Sensor (CGM) in der Gewebsflüssigkeit gemessen und als CGM-(Sensor)Werte in Apple Health gespeichert werden können. In GluVib wird IG angezeigt, sobald CGM-(Sensor)Werte in Apple Health verfügbar sind, und mit visuellem Kontext auf Basis der konfigurierten Schwellenwerte und Zielbereiche dargestellt. Alle IG-Anzeigen basieren auf den in Apple Health verfügbaren und freigegebenen CGM-(Sensor)Daten und dienen der informativen Übersicht."
          }
        },
        "en" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "new",
            "value" : "IG stands for Interstitial Glucose (tissue glucose). It refers to glucose values measured by a continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) (Sensor) sensor in the interstitial fluid and recorded as CGM (Sensor) samples in Apple Health. In GluVib, IG is displayed as soon as CGM (Sensor) values are available in Apple Health and is shown with visual context based on the configured thresholds and target range. All IG displays are based on the CGM (Sensor) data available in Apple Health and are presented for informational review."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "faq.glossary.ig.question" : {
      "comment" : "Question asking what IG means in the glossary",
      "extractionState" : "extracted_with_value",
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
